    {
        "content": "<p>Alright so I am pretty much stuck until <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/issues/6370\">https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/issues/6370</a> is solved. There is no other way to start using the new wasm component model on a Host/Guest setup. Right?  <span aria-label=\"sob\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f62d\" role=\"img\" title=\"sob\">:sob:</span></p>\n<div class=\"message_embed\"><a class=\"message_embed_image\" href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/issues/6370\" style=\"background-image: url(https\\:\\/\\/uploads\\.zulipusercontent\\.net\\/b702676b9a3d74d37798edc3f5b33772df7c650f\\/68747470733a2f2f6f70656e67726170682e6769746875626173736574732e636f6d2f313838373235343664363262366534363235393462333733333737613035343662396163353838643433663834313433636335666631363061303031303635392f62797465636f6465616c6c69616e63652f7761736d74696d652f6973737565732f36333730)\"></a><div class=\"data-container\"><div class=\"message_embed_title\"><a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/issues/6370\" title=\"Land WASI Preview 2 support into Wasmtime 路 Issue #6370 路 bytecodealliance/wasmtime\">Land WASI Preview 2 support into Wasmtime 路 Issue #6370 路 bytecodealliance/wasmtime</a></div><div class=\"message_embed_description\">We have been working on a prototype of what WASI Preview 2 support will look like in Wasmtime for 7 months now! https://github.com/bytecodealliance/preview2-prototyping/ The work is not yet totally...</div></div></div>",
